  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "US-Iran ceasefire announcement triggers classic risk-on rotation with oil diving below $100, dollar weakening, and crypto/equities surging as geopolitical premium unwinds. Energy supply shock concerns are moderating but volatility expected to persist, while traditional safe havens like gold paradoxically rally alongside risk assets.",
    "regimeImpact": "This reinforces the oversold relief rally thesis as geopolitical tail risk reduction allows focus to return to underlying bear market fundamentals, but doesn't change the structural regime given oil still near $100 and core stresses remain.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder closely as ETH whale accumulation and $2,500 technical break could accelerate assignment risk on cash-secured puts",
      "Consider reducing short book exposure temporarily as relief rally has fundamental catalyst and could extend further with continued risk-on flows",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight as falling yields benefit duration plays despite temporary risk-on rotation"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil breaking below $100 removes immediate stagflation pressure but analysts expect continued volatility.",
      "Dollar weakness and falling yields suggest Fed pivot expectations may be returning to market pricing.",
      "BTC above $70K and ETH approaching $2,500 with whale accumulation signals crypto risk-on acceleration.",
      "Gold rallying despite risk-on suggests underlying inflation/debasement concerns persist beyond geopolitical premium."
    ]
